org.pac4j.play

Class ApplicationLogoutController

  • java.lang.Object
    • play.mvc.Results
      • play.mvc.Controller
        • org.pac4j.play.ApplicationLogoutController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    play.mvc.Http.HeaderNames, play.mvc.Http.Status

    public class ApplicationLogoutController
extends play.mvc.Controller

    This controller handles the application logout process.

    After logout, the user is redirected to the url defined by the url parameter. If no url is provided, a blank page is displayed. If the url does not match the pattern, the default url is used.

    The default url can be defined via the setDefaultUrl(String) method.

    The logout url pattern can be defined via the setLogoutUrlPattern(String) method.

    Since:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Jerome Leleu
